30/* The implicit \0 is useless, but we do not write num_to_text[62] otherwise
31 g++ complains. */
32static const char num_to_text36[] = "0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
33static const char num_to_text62[] = "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ"
34 "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
35
36/* copy most important limbs of {op, n2} in {rp, n1} */
37/* if n1 > n2 put 0 in low limbs of {rp, n1} */
38#define MPN_COPY2(rp, n1, op, n2) \
39 if ((n1) <= (n2)) \
40 { \
41 MPN_COPY ((rp), (op) + (n2) - (n1), (n1)); \
42 } \
43 else \
44 { \
45 MPN_COPY ((rp) + (n1) - (n2), (op), (n2)); \
46 MPN_ZERO ((rp), (n1) - (n2)); \
47 }
48
49#define MPFR_ROUND_FAILED 3
50
51/* Input: an approximation r*2^f to a real Y, with |r*2^f - Y| <= 2^(e+f).
52
53 If rounding is possible, returns:
54 - in s: a string representing the significand corresponding to
55 the integer nearest to Y, within the direction rnd;
56 - in exp: the exponent.
57
58 n is the number of limbs of r.
59 e represents the maximal error in the approximation to Y (see above),
60 (e < 0 means that the approximation is known to be exact, i.e.,
61 r*2^f = Y).
62 b is the wanted base (2 <= b <= 62 or -36 <= b <= -2).
63 m is the number of wanted digits in the significand.
64 rnd is the rounding mode.
65 It is assumed that b^(m-1) <= Y < b^(m+1), thus the returned value
66 satisfies b^(m-1) <= rnd(Y) < b^(m+1).
67
68 Rounding may fail for two reasons:
69 - the error is too large to determine the integer N nearest to Y
70 - either the number of digits of N in base b is too large (m+1),
71 N=2*N1+(b/2) and the rounding mode is to nearest. This can
72 only happen when b is even.
73
74 Return value:
75 - the direction of rounding (-1, 0, 1) if rounding is possible
76 - -MPFR_ROUND_FAILED if rounding not possible because m+1 digits
77 - MPFR_ROUND_FAILED otherwise (too large error)
78*/
79static int
80mpfr_get_str_aux (char *const str, mpfr_exp_t *const exp, mp_limb_t *const r,
81 mp_size_t n, mpfr_exp_t f, long e, int b, size_t m,
82 mpfr_rnd_t rnd)
83{
84 const char *num_to_text;
85 int b0 = b; /* initial base (might be negative) */
86 int dir; /* direction of the rounded result */
87 mp_limb_t ret = 0; /* possible carry in addition */
88 mp_size_t i0, j0; /* number of limbs and bits of Y */
89 unsigned char *str1; /* string of m+2 characters */
90 size_t size_s1; /* length of str1 */
91 mpfr_rnd_t rnd1;
92 size_t i;
93 int exact = (e < 0);
94 MPFR_TMP_DECL(marker);
95
96 /* if f > 0, then the maximal error 2^(e+f) is larger than 2 so we can't
97 determine the integer Y */
98 MPFR_ASSERTN(f <= 0);
99 /* if f is too small, then r*2^f is smaller than 1 */
100 MPFR_ASSERTN(f > (-n * GMP_NUMB_BITS));
101
102 MPFR_TMP_MARK(marker);
103
104 num_to_text = (2 <= b0 && b0 <= 36) ? num_to_text36 : num_to_text62;
105 b = (b0 > 0) ? b0 : -b0;
106
107 /* R = 2^f sum r[i]K^(i)
108 r[i] = (r_(i,k-1)...r_(i,0))_2
109 R = sum r(i,j)2^(j+ki+f)
110 the bits from R are referenced by pairs (i,j) */
111
112 /* check if is possible to round r with rnd mode
113 where |r*2^f - Y| <= 2^(e+f)
114 the exponent of R is: f + n*GMP_NUMB_BITS
115 we must have e + f == f + n*GMP_NUMB_BITS - err
116 err = n*GMP_NUMB_BITS - e
117 R contains exactly -f bits after the integer point:
118 to determine the nearest integer, we thus need a precision of
119 n * GMP_NUMB_BITS + f */
120
121 if (exact || mpfr_round_p (r, n, n * GMP_NUMB_BITS - e,
122 n * GMP_NUMB_BITS + f + (rnd == MPFR_RNDN)))
123 {
124 /* compute the nearest integer to R */
125
126 /* bit of weight 0 in R has position j0 in limb r[i0] */
127 i0 = (-f) / GMP_NUMB_BITS;
128 j0 = (-f) % GMP_NUMB_BITS;
129
130 ret = mpfr_round_raw (r + i0, r, n * GMP_NUMB_BITS, 0,
131 n * GMP_NUMB_BITS + f, rnd, &dir);
132 MPFR_ASSERTD(dir != MPFR_ROUND_FAILED);
133
134 if (ret) /* Y is a power of 2 */
135 {
136 if (j0)
137 r[n - 1] = MPFR_LIMB_HIGHBIT >> (j0 - 1);
138 else /* j0=0, necessarily i0 >= 1 otherwise f=0 and r is exact */
139 {
140 r[n - 1] = ret;
141 r[--i0] = 0; /* set to zero the new low limb */
142 }
143 }
144 else /* shift r to the right by (-f) bits (i0 already done) */
145 {
146 if (j0)
147 mpn_rshift (r + i0, r + i0, n - i0, j0);
148 }
149
150 /* now the rounded value Y is in {r+i0, n-i0} */
151
152 /* convert r+i0 into base b: we use b0 which might be in -36..-2 */
153 str1 = (unsigned char*) MPFR_TMP_ALLOC (m + 3); /* need one extra character for mpn_get_str */
154 size_s1 = mpn_get_str (str1, b, r + i0, n - i0);
155
156 /* round str1 */
157 MPFR_ASSERTN(size_s1 >= m);
158 *exp = size_s1 - m; /* number of superfluous characters */
159
160 /* if size_s1 = m + 2, necessarily we have b^(m+1) as result,
161 and the result will not change */
162
163 /* so we have to double-round only when size_s1 = m + 1 and
164 (i) the result is inexact
165 (ii) or the last digit is non-zero */
166 if ((size_s1 == m + 1) && ((dir != 0) || (str1[size_s1 - 1] != 0)))
167 {
168 /* rounding mode */
169 rnd1 = rnd;
170
171 /* round to nearest case */
172 if (rnd == MPFR_RNDN)
173 {
174 if (2 * str1[size_s1 - 1] == b)
175 {
176 if (dir == 0 && exact) /* exact: even rounding */
177 {
178 rnd1 = ((str1[size_s1 - 2] & 1) == 0)
179 ? MPFR_RNDD : MPFR_RNDU;
180 }
181 else
182 {
183 /* otherwise we cannot round correctly: for example
184 if b=10, we might have a mantissa of
185 xxxxxxx5.00000000 which can be rounded to nearest
186 to 8 digits but not to 7 */
187 dir = -MPFR_ROUND_FAILED;
188 MPFR_ASSERTD(dir != MPFR_EVEN_INEX);
189 goto free_and_return;
190 }
191 }
192 else if (2 * str1[size_s1 - 1] < b)
193 rnd1 = MPFR_RNDD;
194 else
195 rnd1 = MPFR_RNDU;
196 }
197
198 /* now rnd1 is either
199 MPFR_RNDD or MPFR_RNDZ -> truncate, or
200 MPFR_RNDU or MPFR_RNDA -> round toward infinity */
201
202 /* round away from zero */
203 if (rnd1 == MPFR_RNDU || rnd1 == MPFR_RNDA)
204 {
205 if (str1[size_s1 - 1] != 0)
206 {
207 /* the carry cannot propagate to the whole string, since
208 Y = x*b^(m-g) < 2*b^m <= b^(m+1)-b
209 where x is the input float */
210 MPFR_ASSERTN(size_s1 >= 2);
211 i = size_s1 - 2;
212 while (str1[i] == b - 1)
213 {
214 MPFR_ASSERTD(i > 0);
215 str1[i--] = 0;
216 }
217 str1[i]++;
218 }
219 dir = 1;
220 }
221 /* round toward zero (truncate) */
222 else
223 dir = -1;
224 }
225
226 /* copy str1 into str and convert to characters (digits and
227 lowercase letters from the source character set) */
228 for (i = 0; i < m; i++)
229 str[i] = num_to_text[(int) str1[i]]; /* str1[i] is an unsigned char */
230 str[m] = 0;
231 }
232 /* mpfr_can_round_raw failed: rounding is not possible */
233 else
234 {
235 dir = MPFR_ROUND_FAILED; /* should be different from MPFR_EVEN_INEX */
236 MPFR_ASSERTD(dir != MPFR_EVEN_INEX);
237 }
238
239 free_and_return:
240 MPFR_TMP_FREE(marker);
241
242 return dir;
243}

2211/* returns ceil(e * log2(b)^((-1)^i)), or ... + 1.
2212 For i=0, uses a 23-bit upper approximation to log(beta)/log(2).
2213 For i=1, uses a 77-bit upper approximation to log(2)/log(beta).
2214 Note: this function should be called only in the extended exponent range.
2215*/
2216mpfr_exp_t
2217mpfr_ceil_mul (mpfr_exp_t e, int beta, int i)
2218{
2219 mpfr_srcptr p;
2220 mpfr_t t;
2221 mpfr_exp_t r;
2222 mp_limb_t tmpmant[MPFR_EXP_LIMB_SIZE];
2223
2224 p = &__gmpfr_l2b[beta-2][i];
2225 MPFR_TMP_INIT1(tmpmant, t, sizeof (mpfr_exp_t) * CHAR_BIT - 1);
2226 mpfr_set_exp_t (t, e, MPFR_RNDU);
2227 mpfr_mul (t, t, p, MPFR_RNDU);
2228 r = mpfr_get_exp_t (t, MPFR_RNDU);
2229 return r;
2230}

2232/* prints the mantissa of x in the string s, and writes the corresponding
2233 exponent in e.
2234 x is rounded with direction rnd, m is the number of digits of the mantissa,
2235 |b| is the given base (2 <= b <= 62 or -36 <= b <= -2).
2236
2237 Return value:
2238 if s=NULL, allocates a string to store the mantissa, with
2239 m characters, plus a final '\0', plus a possible minus sign
2240 (thus m+1 or m+2 characters).
2241
2242 Important: when you call this function with s=NULL, don't forget to free
2243 the memory space allocated, with mpfr_free_str.
2244*/
2245char*
2246mpfr_get_str (char *s, mpfr_exp_t *e, int b, size_t m, mpfr_srcptr x,
2247 mpfr_rnd_t rnd)
2248{
2249 const char *num_to_text;
2250 int exact; /* exact result */
2251 mpfr_exp_t exp, g;
2252 mpfr_exp_t prec; /* precision of the computation */
2253 long err;
2254 mp_limb_t *a;
2255 mpfr_exp_t exp_a;
2256 mp_limb_t *result;
2257 mp_limb_t *xp;
2258 mp_limb_t *reste;
2259 size_t nx, nx1;
2260 size_t n, i;
2261 char *s0;
2262 int neg;
2263 int ret; /* return value of mpfr_get_str_aux */
2264 int b0 = b; /* initial base argument, might be negative */
2265 MPFR_ZIV_DECL (loop);
2266 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_DECL (expo);
2267 MPFR_TMP_DECL (marker);
2268
2269 /* if exact = 1 then err is undefined */
2270 /* otherwise err is such that |x*b^(m-g)-a*2^exp_a| < 2^(err+exp_a) */
2271
2272 MPFR_LOG_FUNC
2273 (("b=%d m=%zu x[%Pu]=%.*Rg rnd=%d",
2274 b, m, mpfr_get_prec (x), mpfr_log_prec, x, rnd),
2275 ("flags=%lx", (unsigned long) __gmpfr_flags));
2276
2277 /* Is the base argument valid? Valid values are -36 to -2 and 2 to 62. */
2278 if (b < -36 || (-2 < b && b < 2) || 62 < b)
2279 return NULL;
2280
2281 num_to_text = (2 <= b && b <= 36) ? num_to_text36 : num_to_text62;
2282
2283 b = (b > 0) ? b : -b;
2284
2285 /* now b is positive */
2286
2287 /* map RNDF to RNDN, to avoid problems with specification of mpfr_can_round
2288 or mpfr_can_round_raw */
2289 if (rnd == MPFR_RNDF)
2290 rnd = MPFR_RNDN;
2291
2292 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (MPFR_IS_NAN (x)))
2293 {
2294 if (s == NULL)
2295 s = (char *) mpfr_allocate_func (6);
2296 strcpy (s, "@NaN@");
2297 MPFR_LOG_MSG (("%s\n", s));
2298 __gmpfr_flags |= MPFR_FLAGS_NAN;
2299 return s;
2300 }
2301
2302 neg = MPFR_IS_NEG (x); /* 0 if positive, 1 if negative */
2303
2304 if (MPFR_UNLIKELY (MPFR_IS_INF (x)))
2305 {
2306 if (s == NULL)
2307 s = (char *) mpfr_allocate_func (neg + 6);
2308 strcpy (s, (neg) ? "-@Inf@" : "@Inf@");
2309 MPFR_LOG_MSG (("%s\n", s));
2310 return s;
2311 }
2312
2313 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_MARK (expo); /* needed for mpfr_ceil_mul (at least) */
2314
2315 if (m == 0)
2316 {
2317
2318 /* take at least 1 + ceil(n*log(2)/log(b)) digits, where n is the
2319 number of bits of the mantissa, to ensure back conversion from
2320 the output gives the same floating-point.
2321
2322 Warning: if b = 2^k, this may be too large. The worst case is when
2323 the first base-b digit contains only one bit, so we get
2324 1 + ceil((n-1)/k) = 2 + floor((n-2)/k) instead.
2325 */
2326 m = 1 +
2327 mpfr_ceil_mul (IS_POW2(b) ? MPFR_PREC(x) - 1 : MPFR_PREC(x), b, 1);
2328 if (m < 2)
2329 m = 2;
2330 }
2331
2332 MPFR_LOG_MSG (("m=%zu\n", m));
2333
2334 /* The code below for non-power-of-two bases works for m=1;
2335 this is important for the internal use of mpfr_get_str. */
2336 MPFR_ASSERTN (m >= 2 || (!IS_POW2(b) && m >= 1));
2337
2338 /* x is a floating-point number */
2339
2340 if (s == NULL)
2341 s = (char *) mpfr_allocate_func (neg + m + 1);
2342 s0 = s;
2343 if (neg)
2344 *s++ = '-';
2345
2346 if (MPFR_IS_ZERO (x))
2347 {
2348 memset (s, '0', m);
2349 s[m] = '\0';
2350 *e = 0; /* a bit like frexp() in ISO C99 */
2351 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
2352 return s0; /* strlen(s0) = neg + m */
2353 }
2354
2355 xp = MPFR_MANT (x);
2356
2357 if (IS_POW2 (b))
2358 {
2359 int pow2;
2360 mpfr_exp_t f, r;
2361 mp_limb_t *x1;
2362 mp_size_t nb;
2363 int inexp;
2364
2365 count_leading_zeros (pow2, (mp_limb_t) b);
2366 pow2 = GMP_NUMB_BITS - pow2 - 1; /* base = 2^pow2 */
2367
2368 /* set MPFR_EXP(x) = f*pow2 + r, 1 <= r <= pow2 */
2369 f = (MPFR_GET_EXP (x) - 1) / pow2;
2370 r = MPFR_GET_EXP (x) - f * pow2;
2371 if (r <= 0)
2372 {
2373 f --;
2374 r += pow2;
2375 }
2376
2377 /* the first digit will contain only r bits */
2378 prec = (m - 1) * pow2 + r; /* total number of bits */
2379 n = MPFR_PREC2LIMBS (prec);
2380
2381 MPFR_TMP_MARK (marker);
2382 x1 = MPFR_TMP_LIMBS_ALLOC (n + 1);
2383 nb = n * GMP_NUMB_BITS - prec;
2384 /* round xp to the precision prec, and put it into x1
2385 put the carry into x1[n] */
2386 if ((x1[n] = mpfr_round_raw (x1, xp, MPFR_PREC(x),
2387 MPFR_IS_STRICTNEG(x),
2388 prec, rnd, &inexp)))
2389 {
2390 /* overflow when rounding x: x1 = 2^prec */
2391 if (r == pow2) /* prec = m * pow2,
2392 2^prec will need (m+1) digits in base 2^pow2 */
2393 {
2394 /* divide x1 by 2^pow2, and increase the exponent */
2395 mpn_rshift (x1, x1, n + 1, pow2);
2396 f ++;
2397 }
2398 else /* 2^prec needs still m digits, but x1 may need n+1 limbs */
2399 n ++;
2400 }
2401
2402 /* it remains to shift x1 by nb limbs to the right, since mpn_get_str
2403 expects a right-normalized number */
2404 if (nb != 0)
2405 {
2406 mpn_rshift (x1, x1, n, nb);
2407 /* the most significant word may be zero */
2408 if (x1[n - 1] == 0)
2409 n --;
2410 }
2411
2412 mpn_get_str ((unsigned char *) s, b, x1, n);
2413 for (i = 0; i < m; i++)
2414 s[i] = num_to_text[(int) s[i]];
2415 s[m] = 0;
2416
2417 /* the exponent of s is f + 1 */
2418 *e = f + 1;
2419
2420 MPFR_LOG_MSG (("e=%" MPFR_EXP_FSPEC "d\n", (mpfr_eexp_t) *e));
2421
2422 MPFR_TMP_FREE (marker);
2423 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
2424 return s0;
2425 }
2426
2427 /* if x < 0, reduce to x > 0 */
2428 if (neg)
2429 rnd = MPFR_INVERT_RND (rnd);
2430
2431 g = mpfr_ceil_mul (MPFR_GET_EXP (x) - 1, b, 1);
2432 exact = 1;
2433 prec = mpfr_ceil_mul (m, b, 0) + 1;
2434 exp = ((mpfr_exp_t) m < g) ? g - (mpfr_exp_t) m : (mpfr_exp_t) m - g;
2435 prec += MPFR_INT_CEIL_LOG2 (prec); /* number of guard bits */
2436 if (exp != 0) /* add maximal exponentiation error */
2437 prec += 3 * (mpfr_exp_t) MPFR_INT_CEIL_LOG2 (exp);
2438
2439 MPFR_ZIV_INIT (loop, prec);
2440 for (;;)
2441 {
2442 MPFR_TMP_MARK (marker);
2443
2444 exact = 1;
2445
2446 /* number of limbs */
2447 n = MPFR_PREC2LIMBS (prec);
2448
2449 /* a will contain the approximation of the mantissa */
2450 a = MPFR_TMP_LIMBS_ALLOC (n);
2451
2452 nx = MPFR_LIMB_SIZE (x);
2453
2454 if ((mpfr_exp_t) m == g) /* final exponent is 0, no multiplication or
2455 division to perform */
2456 {
2457 if (nx > n)
2458 exact = mpn_scan1 (xp, 0) >= (nx - n) * GMP_NUMB_BITS;
2459 err = !exact;
2460 MPN_COPY2 (a, n, xp, nx);
2461 exp_a = MPFR_GET_EXP (x) - n * GMP_NUMB_BITS;
2462 }
2463 else if ((mpfr_exp_t) m > g) /* we have to multiply x by b^exp */
2464 {
2465 mp_limb_t *x1;
2466
2467 /* a2*2^exp_a = b^e */
2468 err = mpfr_mpn_exp (a, &exp_a, b, exp, n);
2469 /* here, the error on a is at most 2^err ulps */
2470 exact = (err == -1);
2471
2472 /* x = x1*2^(n*GMP_NUMB_BITS) */
2473 x1 = (nx >= n) ? xp + nx - n : xp;
2474 nx1 = (nx >= n) ? n : nx; /* nx1 = min(n, nx) */
2475
2476 /* test si exact */
2477 if (nx > n)
2478 exact = (exact &&
2479 ((mpn_scan1 (xp, 0) >= (nx - n) * GMP_NUMB_BITS)));
2480
2481 /* we loose one more bit in the multiplication,
2482 except when err=0 where we loose two bits */
2483 err = (err <= 0) ? 2 : err + 1;
2484
2485 /* result = a * x */
2486 result = MPFR_TMP_LIMBS_ALLOC (n + nx1);
2487 mpn_mul (result, a, n, x1, nx1);
2488 exp_a += MPFR_GET_EXP (x);
2489 if (mpn_scan1 (result, 0) < (nx1 * GMP_NUMB_BITS))
2490 exact = 0;
2491
2492 /* normalize a and truncate */
2493 if ((result[n + nx1 - 1] & MPFR_LIMB_HIGHBIT) == 0)
2494 {
2495 mpn_lshift (a, result + nx1, n , 1);
2496 a[0] |= result[nx1 - 1] >> (GMP_NUMB_BITS - 1);
2497 exp_a --;
2498 }
2499 else
2500 MPN_COPY (a, result + nx1, n);
2501 }
2502 else
2503 {
2504 mp_limb_t *x1;
2505
2506 /* a2*2^exp_a = b^e */
2507 err = mpfr_mpn_exp (a, &exp_a, b, exp, n);
2508 exact = (err == -1);
2509
2510 /* allocate memory for x1, result and reste */
2511 x1 = MPFR_TMP_LIMBS_ALLOC (2 * n);
2512 result = MPFR_TMP_LIMBS_ALLOC (n + 1);
2513 reste = MPFR_TMP_LIMBS_ALLOC (n);
2514
2515 /* initialize x1 = x */
2516 MPN_COPY2 (x1, 2 * n, xp, nx);
2517 if ((exact) && (nx > 2 * n) &&
2518 (mpn_scan1 (xp, 0) < (nx - 2 * n) * GMP_NUMB_BITS))
2519 exact = 0;
2520
2521 /* result = x / a */
2522 mpn_tdiv_qr (result, reste, 0, x1, 2 * n, a, n);
2523 exp_a = MPFR_GET_EXP (x) - exp_a - 2 * n * GMP_NUMB_BITS;
2524
2525 /* test if division was exact */
2526 if (exact)
2527 exact = mpn_popcount (reste, n) == 0;
2528
2529 /* normalize the result and copy into a */
2530 if (result[n] == 1)
2531 {
2532 mpn_rshift (a, result, n, 1);
2533 a[n - 1] |= MPFR_LIMB_HIGHBIT;;
2534 exp_a ++;
2535 }
2536 else
2537 MPN_COPY (a, result, n);
2538
2539 err = (err == -1) ? 2 : err + 2;
2540 }
2541
2542 /* check if rounding is possible */
2543 if (exact)
2544 err = -1;
2545
2546 ret = mpfr_get_str_aux (s, e, a, n, exp_a, err, b0, m, rnd);
2547
2548 MPFR_TMP_FREE (marker);
2549
2550 if (ret == MPFR_ROUND_FAILED)
2551 {
2552 /* too large error: increment the working precision */
2553 MPFR_ZIV_NEXT (loop, prec);
2554 }
2555 else if (ret == - MPFR_ROUND_FAILED)
2556 {
2557 /* too many digits in mantissa: exp = |m-g| */
2558 if ((mpfr_exp_t) m > g) /* exp = m - g, multiply by b^exp */
2559 {
2560 g ++;
2561 exp --;
2562 }
2563 else /* exp = g - m, divide by b^exp */
2564 {
2565 g ++;
2566 exp ++;
2567 }
2568 }
2569 else
2570 {
2571 if (ret != 0)
2572 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_UPDATE_FLAGS (expo, MPFR_FLAGS_INEXACT);
2573 break;
2574 }
2575 }
2576 MPFR_ZIV_FREE (loop);
2577
2578 *e += g;
2579
2580 MPFR_LOG_MSG (("e=%" MPFR_EXP_FSPEC "d\n", (mpfr_eexp_t) *e));
2581
2582 MPFR_SAVE_EXPO_FREE (expo);
2583 return s0;
2584}
